<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[188,1400,1472,1958]" box="[189,322,1472,1501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,322,1472,1501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[188,1400,1472,1958]" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">
Head, pronotum, mesonotum, and forewings finely shagreened by punctation. Metope (frons) wide, with lateral margins nearly straight or slightly converging above eyes and foliated below eyes hanging over the pedicels (
<figureCitation box="[404,557,1580,1606]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Fig 4B, D, F</figureCitation>
). Metopoclypeal suture nearly straight, deep. Pedicel globular. Rostrum distinctly protruding beyond hind coxae; 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[685,699,1614,1628]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">rd</superScript>
segment long, nearly as long as 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1093,1110,1614,1628]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">nd</superScript>
one, narrowing apically. Eyes 0.5 × as wide as coryphe (vertex) (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[839,935,1650,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[947,985,1650,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,1050,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-275@5.[189,1398,1026,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761688/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[997,1036,1650,1676]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">3A</figureCitation>
). Paradiscal fields of pronotum very narrow behind eyes. Paranotal lobes of pronotum triangular-shaped, with strongly producing lower angle (
<figureCitation box="[270,368,1720,1747]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Scutellum depressed basally. Tegulae narrow, with elongate depression (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1385,1720,1747]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Fig. 4E, G</figureCitation>
). Forewings wide, with reticulate venation, without hypocostal plate, claval suture invisible. Forewing costal margin strongly protruding below eyes (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[927,1087,1791,1817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Fig. 4C, E, G</figureCitation>
). Hind wings rudimentary. Male anal tube with long and narrow column. Male pygofer elongate vertically. Apical aedeagal process long and narrow, pointed, well visible above upper phallobase margins as two filaments (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1343,1861,1888]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">Figs 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1357,1394,1861,1887]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[191,1314,764,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-164@10.[189,1398,761,1890]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Pygofer, anal tube, and basal part of penis, lateral view. B. Penis and connective, lateral view. C. Penis and connective, ventral view. D. Style, lateral view. E. Style, dorsal view. F. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761696/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[189,229,1897,1923]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="81">7A</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with pair of ventral hooks directed basally, nearly straight or strongly curved. Gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1341,264,337]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,344,264,290]" box="[189,344,264,290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,344,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,344,264,290]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1341,311,337]" box="[189,1341,311,337]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
Five species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[492,562,311,337]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[578,669,311,337]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Hainan</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[688,790,311,337]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[802,910,311,337]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Borneo), and 
<collectingCountry box="[1087,1201,311,337]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1217,1329,311,337]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,937,376,403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,937,376,403]" box="[189,937,376,403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,937,376,403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meng, Qin &amp; Wang, 2020" authorityName="Meng, Qin &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[454,937,376,403]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Superciliaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,611,376,403]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Superciliaris</emphasis>
Meng, Qin &amp; Wang, 2020
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="82" type="key">
<key pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
1. Metope and coryphe joined at acute angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[944,1036,423,449]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Metope with distinct median comb or carina in its upper half (
<figureCitation box="[628,723,458,484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[235,1359,1015,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-239@3.[216,1371,1000,1924]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761686/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[738,776,458,484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">4B</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with short ventral hooks (⅓ of aedeagus length) arise nearly medially ............................................................................................................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
– Metope and coryphe joined at nearly right angle (in lateral view) (
<figureCitation box="[998,1093,529,555]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,1050,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-275@5.[189,1398,1026,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761688/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Figs 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1104,1141,529,555]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">3B</figureCitation>
). Metope flat, without comb or with weak carina (
<figureCitation box="[552,648,564,590]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,1050,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-275@5.[189,1398,1026,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761688/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Figs 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[660,696,564,590]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">3C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[708,794,564,590]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[308,1258,279,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[308,1279,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Superciliaris spp., external view (weak carinae and margins are indicated by dotted lines). A–C. S. anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN). A. Half of face and left paranotal lobe, frontal view. B. Face, frontal view. C. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. D–E. S. celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). D. Face, frontal view. E. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. F–G. S. tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH). F. Face, frontal view. G. Tegula and basal part of forewing, lateral view. Abbreviation: sc = sublateral carinae of metope. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761692/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">4D, 4F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with long ventral hooks (
<superScript attach="none" box="[1227,1236,563,577]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">4</superScript>
/ of aedeagus 5 length) arise subapically ................................................................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
2. Generally brown yellowish. Phallobase elongate (in lateral view), with almost straight ventral hooks (
<figureCitation box="[242,335,699,726]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[221,1339,427,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,420,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Superciliaris anichkini sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ZIN), genitalia. A. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view (basal part of penis showed by dotted line).B. Penis (aedeagus shaded) and connective, lateral view. C. Apical part of phallobase inflated in water. D. Penis, ventral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761694/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[356,455,700,726]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1152,1301,699,726]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Superciliaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anichkini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1152,1301,699,726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">S. anichkini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1399,700,726]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
– Generally dark brown. Phallobase wide (in lateral view), with strongly curved ventral hooks (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang Y. &amp; Che Y. &amp; Meng R. &amp; Wang Y." pageId="2" pageNumber="82" refId="ref5369" refString="Zhang Y., Che Y., Meng R. &amp; Wang Y. 2020. Hemiptera. Caliscelidae. Issidae. Insecta. Fauna Sinica 70, Science Press, Beijing." type="book" year="2020">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[234,293,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 
<quantity box="[425,486,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.16" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" unit="g" value="116.0">116g</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[497,557,770,796]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.17" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" unit="g" value="117.0">117g</quantity>
) ............................................................................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
3. Male anal tube with angularly convex posterior margin (in dorsal view) (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang Y. &amp; Che Y. &amp; Meng R. &amp; Wang Y." box="[1067,1276,835,862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" refId="ref5369" refString="Zhang Y., Che Y., Meng R. &amp; Wang Y. 2020. Hemiptera. Caliscelidae. Issidae. Insecta. Fauna Sinica 70, Science Press, Beijing." type="book" year="2020">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[1148,1205,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 116f). 
<collectingCountry box="[234,304,871,897]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[320,520,871,897]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Hainan Province</collectingRegion>
) .................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Meng, Qin &amp; Wang, 2020" authorityName="Meng, Qin &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2020" box="[924,1399,870,897]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Superciliaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[924,1086,870,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">S. reticulatus</emphasis>
Meng, Qin &amp; Wang, 2020
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
– Male anal tube with weakly convex posterior margin (in dorsal view) (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang Y. &amp; Che Y. &amp; Meng R. &amp; Wang Y." box="[1059,1272,906,932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" refId="ref5369" refString="Zhang Y., Che Y., Meng R. &amp; Wang Y. 2020. Hemiptera. Caliscelidae. Issidae. Insecta. Fauna Sinica 70, Science Press, Beijing." type="book" year="2020">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[1143,1202,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 117f). 
<collectingCountry box="[234,304,941,967]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[320,520,941,967]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Hainan Province</collectingRegion>
) .............................................. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[883,1086,941,968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">S. diaoluoshanis</emphasis>
Meng, Qin &amp; Wang, 2020
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
4. Coryphe nearly 2.5× as wide as long at midline (
<figureCitation box="[812,907,1006,1033]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[239,1345,966,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-176@7.[224,1364,956,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Head, pro- and mesonotum dark brown. Style with nearly straight hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[697,789,1042,1068]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
). Male anal tube distinctly enlarged from its base to its apex (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[534,627,1077,1103]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[187,230,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[259,1323,598,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-121@11.[212,1376,554,1890]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Superciliaris tawaiensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Penis, lateral view.B. Penis, ventral view. C. Anal tube, dorsal view. D. Anal tube, lateral view. E. Style, lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761698/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[648,756,1077,1103]" name="Malaysia" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[771,846,1077,1103]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Sabah</collectingRegion>
) ...................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Gnezdilov, 2022" authorityName="Gnezdilov" authorityYear="2022" box="[1143,1301,1077,1103]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Superciliaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tawaiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1143,1301,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">S. tawaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1399,1077,1103]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,423,1209]" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="82">
– Coryphe twice as wide as long at midline (
<figureCitation box="[743,838,1112,1138]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[215,1374,1050,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-275@5.[189,1398,1026,1926]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), external view. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view. C. Frontal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761688/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Head, pro- and mesonotum light yellow, with dense black dots. Style with deeply concave hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[915,1009,1147,1173]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[191,1314,764,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-164@10.[189,1398,761,1890]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Pygofer, anal tube, and basal part of penis, lateral view. B. Penis and connective, lateral view. C. Penis and connective, ventral view. D. Style, lateral view. E. Style, dorsal view. F. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761696/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Male anal tube equally wide (in dorsal view) (
<figureCitation box="[396,485,1182,1208]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[191,1314,764,1837]" captionTargetId="figure-164@10.[189,1398,761,1890]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. Superciliaris celebensis sp. nov., ♂, holotype (BMNH), genitalia. A. Pygofer, anal tube, and basal part of penis, lateral view. B. Penis and connective, lateral view. C. Penis and connective, ventral view. D. Style, lateral view. E. Style, dorsal view. F. Anal tube, dorsal view. No to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761696/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[506,620,1182,1208]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[636,745,1182,1208]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="82">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
) .................................................... 
